<section id="verify" class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-[#1c1c27]">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center">
      <span class="block text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-[#67e8f9] mb-4">Open &amp; auditable</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-5">
        Verify it yourself
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Graphnosis is <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">source-available under the Functional Source License (FSL-1.1)</span>. You can read the entire app — every line of how it ingests, recalls, and encrypts your Cortex — and fork it, audit it, or build it yourself. FSL forbids exactly one thing: you may not resell Graphnosis as a competing commercial service. And even that restriction expires — each release converts to the fully-permissive Apache&nbsp;2.0 two years after it ships.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] mb-8">
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Watch the network</span>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Read the encryption code</span>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Decrypt your own Cortex</span>
      </p>
      <a
        href="/guides/verify-it-yourself"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-[#67e8f9] hover:bg-[#4dd6e8] text-[#13131a] font-bold text-base transition-colors"
      >
        Read the Verify It Yourself guide
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-[#2a2a3d] mt-12 pt-8">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono tracking-widest text-[#555570] uppercase mb-4">Source &amp; licenses</p>
      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <li class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] leading-relaxed">
          <a href="https://github.com/nehloo-interactive/graphnosis-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono">graphnosis-app</a>
          — the Graphnosis desktop app. <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">FSL-1.1</span>.
        </li>
        <li class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] leading-relaxed">
          <a href="https://github.com/nehloo-interactive/graphnosis-secure-sync" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono">graphnosis-secure-sync</a>
          — the encryption layer: XChaCha20-Poly1305 authenticated encryption and Argon2id key derivation. <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">FSL-1.1</span>.
        </li>
        <li class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] leading-relaxed">
          <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@nehloo/graphnosis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#67e8f9] hover:underline font-mono">@nehloo/graphnosis</a>
          — the engram graph engine and the <code class="text-[#67e8f9] font-mono">.gai</code> graph format. <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Apache-2.0</span>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
